The paper discusses the use of a hybrid K-means and regression classification methodology for anomaly detection, which is a common topic in machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG, cs.AI). The random cluster model is used to define an upper bound on a distance measure, which falls under the category of data mining (cs.DM). The paper also mentions the use of a neural network model for decision region-separating surface, which is a common topic in neural networks (cs.NE) and signal processing (cs.SI).
